        "text": "Based on my exploration, here's a comprehensive overview of the debugging capabilities available in this OpenClaw environment:\n\n## Immediate Debugging Capabilities\n\n### Core Debugging Tools Available:\n1. **Session Management & Monitoring**\n   - `session_status` - Real-time session status with usage metrics\n   - `sessions_list` - View all active sessions and their states\n   - `sessions_history` - Inspect transcript history of any session\n   - `subagents` - List, steer, or kill spawned sub-agents\n\n2. **Process & Execution Debugging**\n   - `exec` - Run shell commands with background continuation\n   - `process` - Manage background exec sessions (list, poll, log, write, kill)\n   - Supports TTY-required commands with `pty: true`\n   - Real-time process monitoring and output capture\n\n3. **System Inspection Tools**\n   - `gateway` - Restart, config inspection, and updates\n   - `cron` - Job scheduling and wake events\n   - `nodes` - Device discovery and control (camera, screen, notifications)\n\n### Hidden State in ~/.openclaw/state:\n- Contains `internal.json` with plugin information\n- Currently shows: `{\"plugins\":[\"status-skill\"],\"workflows\":[\"reminder-workflow\"]}`\n- Limited debugging info in state directory\n\n## Advanced Debugging Features\n\n### Runtime Debug Overrides:\n- `/debug` command for runtime config overrides (when enabled)\n- Raw stream logging capabilities\n- Gateway watch mode for fast iteration\n\n### Logging & Tracing:\n- Raw assistant stream logging (`OPENCLAW_RAW_STREAM`)\n- Raw chunk logging for OpenAI-compatible providers\n- Session-scoped logs and transcripts\n\n### Browser & UI Debugging:\n- `browser` tool with full automation capabilities\n- `canvas` tool for UI rendering and evaluation\n- Screenshot and snapshot capabilities\n- ARIA/AI snapshot modes for accessibility debugging\n\n## Security & Audit Tools:\n- Built-in security audit (`openclaw security audit`)\n- Deep security probes available\n- Tool policy restrictions and allowlists\n\n## Key Debugging Workflows:\n\n1. **Session Debugging**: Use `sessions_list` + `sessions_history` to inspect agent behavior\n2. **Process Debugging**: Use `exec` with `process` tool to monitor long-running commands\n3. **System State**: Use `gateway` and `cron` tools to inspect system configuration\n4. **Real-time Monitoring**: Use `session_status` for live metrics\n\nThe environment provides comprehensive debugging capabilities through both immediate tools and advanced logging/tracing features, with the main limitation being that the hidden state directory contains minimal debugging information.",
